        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "test: migrate src/commands tests to shared temp dir helpers",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Migrate 4 test files in `src/commands/` from raw `fs.mkdtemp`/`fs.mkdtempSync` to shared temp dir helpers (`createSuiteTempRootTracker` / `withTempDir`)\n- Files: `doctor-plugin-manifests.test.ts`, `migrate/apply.test.ts`, `doctor-security.test.ts`, `agents.add.test.ts`\n- No user-visible behavior change\n\n## Background\n\nPart of the ongoing temp-dir migration. `createSuiteTempRootTracker()` is the standard helper for suite-scoped temp directories, providing automatic cleanup in `afterAll` and avoiding disk leaks from raw `mkdtemp` calls.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nRelates to gap finding: `tempdir-batch03`\n\n4 test files in `src/commands/` use raw `fs.mkdtemp`/`fs.mkdtempSync` instead of shared helpers, causing:\n1. **Disk leaks** — temp dirs created but never cleaned up (P0: zero `rm` calls)\n2. **Inconsistent patterns** — the project has standardized on shared helpers\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nMigrates Batch 03 test files with no cleanup:\n\n- `doctor-plugin-manifests.test.ts`: tracked array + `makeTrustedBundledPluginsDir` using `mkdtempSync`, never cleaned\n- `migrate/apply.test.ts`: module-level `mkdtempSync` without any cleanup\n- `doctor-security.test.ts`: `fs.mkdtemp` in `withExecApprovalsFile` helper, never cleaned\n- `agents.add.test.ts`: `fs.mkdtemp` in `withAgentsAddStateRoot` helper, never cleaned\n\n## User Impact\n\nTest-only. Reduces `/tmp` pressure, cleaner CI.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: 内部重构，无用户可见行为变化\nReal environment tested: 本地开发环境 (Linux x86_64, Node 24)\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\npnpm test src/commands/doctor-plugin-manifests.test.ts src/commands/migrate/apply.test.ts src/commands/doctor-security.test.ts src/commands/agents.add.test.ts\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```console\n$ pnpm test src/commands/doctor-plugin-manifests.test.ts src/commands/migrate/apply.test.ts src/commands/doctor-security.test.ts src/commands/agents.add.test.ts\n\n Test Files  4 passed (4)\n      Tests  50 passed (50)\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: 50 tests pass across all 4 migrated test files, matching baseline behavior\nWhat was not tested: full CI suite (triggered on push to remote)\n",
        "branch": "fix/gap-tempdir-batch03",
